## Feedback Log Entry

Append to **`docs/design-feedback-log.md`** (newest first):

```markdown
#### FB-151: "On viewports narrower than 320px, the entire page stops scrolling horizontally — nav clipped on right"

**UX Intent:** Functional chrome (nav, footer) must be fully reachable at any viewport width. A nav item that is visible on hover but unreachable by scrolling is a complete interaction failure — worse than being hidden.

**Root Cause:** No `overflow-x: clip` seal on `.siteWrapper` / `html` / `body`. At sub-320px viewports, the nav's `flex-shrink: 0` logo and `white-space: nowrap` link text produce an intrinsic minimum content width that inflates the document root. The browser expands the root element's box to fit, but suppresses horizontal scrollbar on the root (the root box fits the viewport; only content overflows positionally). Result: nav items clipped on the right, no horizontal scroll to reach them.

**Resolution:** Added `overflow-x: clip; min-width: 0` to `.siteWrapper` in `layout.module.scss`, `html` in `globals.scss`, and `body` in `globals.scss`. Added `min-width: 0; width: 100%` to `.navInner`. `clip` is chosen over `hidden` because `hidden` creates a scroll container that breaks `position: sticky`. Codified as AP-073.

**Pattern extracted → `design-anti-patterns.md` AP-073: overflow-x clip vs hidden on document root**
```

---

## Summary of File Changes

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/app/(frontend)/(site)/layout.module.scss` | Add `overflow-x: clip; min-width: 0` to `.siteWrapper` |
| `src/app/globals.scss` | Add `overflow-x: clip` to `html`; add `overflow-x: clip; min-width: 0` to `body` |
| `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss` | Add `min-width: 0; width: 100%` to `.navInner` |
| `docs/design-anti-patterns.md` | Add AP-073, update Category Index + header datestamp |
| `docs/design-feedback-log.md` | Prepend FB-151 |

---

## Principle

> **AP-073 — The root seal rule:** `overflow-x: clip` belongs on `html`, `body`, and every full-width column wrapper that contains `position: sticky` chrome. `clip` is the only CSS overflow value that prevents document-root horizontal inflation without creating a scroll container. Never use `overflow: hidden` on an ancestor of a sticky element — it collapses sticky to that container. Never use `min-width` on any element above the `.contentAreaInner` / `.contentArea` scroll-container boundary — a floor above that boundary inflates the document root and causes phantom-clipping of nav items at narrow viewports.

